57#ifndef OPENSSL_HEADER_CIPHER_INTERNAL_H
58#define OPENSSL_HEADER_CIPHER_INTERNAL_H
59
60#include <openssl/base.h>
61
62#include <openssl/aead.h>
63#include <openssl/aes.h>
64
65#include "../../internal.h"
66#include "../modes/internal.h"
67
68#if defined(__cplusplus)
69extern "C" {
70#endif
71
72
73// EVP_CIPH_MODE_MASK contains the bits of |flags| that represent the mode.
74#define EVP_CIPH_MODE_MASK 0x3f
75
76// EVP_AEAD represents a specific AEAD algorithm.
77struct evp_aead_st {
78 uint8_t key_len;
79 uint8_t nonce_len;
80 uint8_t overhead;
81 uint8_t max_tag_len;
82 int seal_scatter_supports_extra_in;
83
84 // init initialises an |EVP_AEAD_CTX|. If this call returns zero then
85 // |cleanup| will not be called for that context.
86 int (*init)(EVP_AEAD_CTX *, const uint8_t *key, size_t key_len,
87 size_t tag_len);
88 int (*init_with_direction)(EVP_AEAD_CTX *, const uint8_t *key, size_t key_len,
89 size_t tag_len, enum evp_aead_direction_t dir);
90 void (*cleanup)(EVP_AEAD_CTX *);
91
92 int (*open)(const EVP_AEAD_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out, size_t *out_len,
93 size_t max_out_len, const uint8_t *nonce, size_t nonce_len,
94 const uint8_t *in, size_t in_len, const uint8_t *ad,
95 size_t ad_len);
96
97 int (*seal_scatter)(const EVP_AEAD_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out, uint8_t *out_tag,
98 size_t *out_tag_len, size_t max_out_tag_len,
99 const uint8_t *nonce, size_t nonce_len, const uint8_t *in,
100 size_t in_len, const uint8_t *extra_in,
101 size_t extra_in_len, const uint8_t *ad, size_t ad_len);
102
103 int (*open_gather)(const EVP_AEAD_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out,
104 const uint8_t *nonce, size_t nonce_len, const uint8_t *in,
105 size_t in_len, const uint8_t *in_tag, size_t in_tag_len,
106 const uint8_t *ad, size_t ad_len);
107
108 int (*get_iv)(const EVP_AEAD_CTX *ctx, const uint8_t **out_iv,
109 size_t *out_len);
110
111 size_t (*tag_len)(const EVP_AEAD_CTX *ctx, size_t in_Len,
112 size_t extra_in_len);
113};
114
115// aes_ctr_set_key initialises |*aes_key| using |key_bytes| bytes from |key|,
116// where |key_bytes| must either be 16, 24 or 32. If not NULL, |*out_block| is
117// set to a function that encrypts single blocks. If not NULL, |*gcm_key| is
118// initialised to do GHASH with the given key. It returns a function for
119// optimised CTR-mode, or NULL if CTR-mode should be built using |*out_block|.
120ctr128_f aes_ctr_set_key(AES_KEY *aes_key, GCM128_KEY *gcm_key,
121 block128_f *out_block, const uint8_t *key,
122 size_t key_bytes);
123
124#if defined(__cplusplus)
125} // extern C
126#endif
127
128#endif // OPENSSL_HEADER_CIPHER_INTERNAL_H
